::Prowl/Striker::

Prowl lands on the ground, still kissing Iron Raptor. His wings, no 
longer used for keeping the two bots up, hug Iron Raptor closer to 
him.

He was irrationaly happy, and that slightly annoyed him. When Iron 
Raptor relaxed in his arms, though, the annoyance dissapeared to be 
replaced by a giddy feeling. Prowl closes his eyes, relieved that 
Iron Raptor had accepted the kiss.

"Ahem...," a rather embarrased voice came from behind the two bots, 
"Excuse me, but if you two could spare a moment, I'd like to know 
what I've missed."

Prowl's eyes widen as he hears the voice behind him. Keeping one arm 
and one wing around Iron Raptor, he rather reluctantly turns to face 
the bot that had just spoke. His eyes widen even farther as he sees 
the damaged bot.

"Striker!" he says, resisting an irational urge to punch his 
commander in the nose, "Where have you been?"

Striker looks at Prowl and Iron Raptor, one eyebrow slightly raised. 
"To the Matrix and back. Me and Zenyak nearly killed each other."

Prowl nods. "We picked up Zenyak a little while back."

Striker looks at the two bots and grins. "I see that you also picked 
up a ... bonus," he says, looking at Iron Raptor.

Prowl blushes. "Iron Raptor, this is my commander, Striker."
